# Docker — Build Caching

Always use **BuildKit cache mounts** (`--mount=type=cache`) for package managers and any other layer that downloads or compiles external dependencies. This makes rebuilds fast even when dependencies change.

Enable BuildKit: `DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1` (set in CI env or `docker-compose.yml` via `COMPOSE_DOCKER_CLI_BUILD=1 DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1`).

## Python (uv)

```dockerfile
FROM python:3.12-slim

# Install uv
COPY --from=ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:latest /uv /usr/local/bin/uv

WORKDIR /app

COPY pyproject.toml uv.lock ./

# ✅ cache uv's download cache across builds
RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
    uv sync --frozen --no-dev

COPY . .
```

## JavaScript / TypeScript (bun)

```dockerfile
FROM oven/bun:1-alpine AS deps
WORKDIR /app
COPY package.json bun.lock ./

# ✅ cache bun's install cache across builds
RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.bun/install/cache \
    bun install --frozen-lockfile

FROM oven/bun:1-alpine AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=deps /app/node_modules ./node_modules
COPY . .
RUN bun run build

FROM oven/bun:1-alpine AS runtime
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=builder /app/.next ./.next
COPY --from=builder /app/node_modules ./node_modules
COPY --from=builder /app/package.json ./
USER nonroot
CMD ["bun", "run", "start"]
```

Never use `npm ci` or `yarn install` in new Dockerfiles — always `bun install --frozen-lockfile`.

## System packages (apt)

```dockerfile
# ✅ cache apt package index and downloaded .deb files
RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/var/cache/apt,sharing=locked \
    --mount=type=cache,target=/var/lib/apt,sharing=locked \
    apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    curl \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
```

## Multi-stage builds (always use for production images)

```dockerfile
# Stage 1 — install deps with uv
FROM python:3.12-slim AS builder
COPY --from=ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:latest /uv /usr/local/bin/uv
WORKDIR /app
COPY pyproject.toml uv.lock ./
RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
    uv sync --frozen --no-dev --prefix=/install

# Stage 2 — minimal runtime image (no uv, no build tools)
FROM python:3.12-slim AS runtime
COPY --from=builder /install /usr/local
COPY . /app
WORKDIR /app
USER nobody
CMD ["python", "-m", "myapp"]
```

## Rules

- Every `RUN` that installs packages must use `--mount=type=cache`.
- Never use `FROM ... AS latest` or `FROM python:latest` — always pin the version.
- Final stage runs as a non-root user (`USER nobody` or a named user).
- `.dockerignore` must exclude: `.git`, `__pycache__`, `*.pyc`, `node_modules`, `.env*`, `tests/`.
